{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Russia", "text_new": "{{Current disaster|event= disease pandemic|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2020}}\n{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Russia}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Russia\n| width           = \n| map1            = COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in Russia (Density).svg{{!}}350px\n| legend1         = Confirmed total cases by federal subjects\n{{legend|#900000|1,000+}}\n{{legend|#c80200|100\u2013999}}\n{{legend|#ee7070|10\u201399}}\n{{legend|#ffC0C0|1\u20139}}\n{{legend|#e0e0e0| No confirmed cases}}\n| map2            = COVID-19 outbreak cases per capita in Russia.svg{{!}}350px\n| legend2         = Confirmed total cases per capita by federal subjects\n{{legend|#900000| 1\u201310 cases per 10,000 inhabitants}}\n{{legend|#c80200| 1\u201310 cases per 100,000 inhabitants}}\n{{legend|#ee7070| 1\u201310 cases per 1 million inhabitants}}\n{{legend|#ffC0C0| 1\u201310 cases per 10 million inhabitants}}\n{{legend|#e0e0e0| No confirmed cases}}\n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Russia]]\n| first_case      = [[Tyumen]] and [[Chita, Zabaykalsky Krai|Chita]]\n| arrival_date    = 31 January 2020\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], [[China]]\n| recovery_cases  = 281<ref name=\"Rus_Ministry\" /><ref name=\"Rus_Taskforce\" />{{efn|name=\"diamond-princess\"}}\n| deaths          = 34<!--1st death is not included in official statistics--><ref name=\"Rus_Ministry\" /><ref name=\"Rus_Taskforce\" />{{efn|name=mow-death}}\n| confirmed_cases = 4,149<ref name=\"Rus_Ministry\" /><ref name=\"Rus_Taskforce\" />{{efn|name=\"diamond-princess\"}}\n| active_cases    = \n| suspected_cases = \n| total_ili       = \n| website         = \n}}\n\nThe first cases of the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] were confirmed in [[Russia]] on 31 January 2020. Early prevention measures included restricting the [[China-Russia border|border with China]] and extensive testing. Later measures, after the infection spread from [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy|Italy]] on 2 March, included cancelling events, closing schools, theatres and museums, shutting the border, and declaring a non-working period. By the end of March, lockdowns were imposed in the vast majority of [[federal subjects of Russia|federal subjects]], including [[Moscow]].\n\n== Timeline ==\n{{further|Timeline of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\nOn 31 January, two cases were confirmed, one in [[Tyumen]], another in [[Chita, Zabaykalsky Krai|Chita]], [[Zabaykalsky Krai]]. Both were Chinese nationals, who have since recovered.<ref name=\"rusjan31\" /><ref name=\"rusfeb12\" />\n\nOn 23 February, eight Russians from the cruise ship ''[[Diamond Princess outbreak|Diamond Princess]]'' were evacuated to [[Kazan]], [[Tatarstan]] where they were hospitalised, including three confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tass.ru/obschestvo/7843971|title=\u0423 \u0442\u0440\u043e\u0438\u0445 \u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u044f\u043d \u0441 \u043b\u0430\u0439\u043d\u0435\u0440\u0430 Diamond Princess \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0438\u043b\u0441\u044f \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441|date=26 February 2020|publisher=TASS}}</ref> These cases were listed as occurring on international conveyance and not included in official Russian statistics by [[Rospotrebnadzor]]. These eight people, including the three patients who recovered, were discharged from hospital on 8 March.<ref>{{cite news |title=All quarantined Russians from Diamond Princess cruise ship discharged from hospital |url=https://tass.com/russia/1127861 |accessdate=8 March 2020 |work=[[TASS]] |date=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nSome of [[Citizenship of Russia|Russia's citizens]] abroad have been confirmed to be infected, a Russian man tested positive in [[Azerbaijan]] after having visited [[Iran]], it was confirmed on 28 February. While some days later the [[Health ministry of the UAE]] announced that two Russians got the virus in [[United Arab Emirates]].<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\nOn 1 March, one woman had escaped from the hospital in [[Sevastopol]] (in the [[Political status of Crimea|disputed]]-[[Republic of Crimea|Crimea]]) before being checked for the virus. She fled to [[Rostov-on-Don]] and is on the wanted list.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://112.international/society/woman-in-sevastopil-escaped-from-hospital-before-checking-for-coronavirus-49063-amp.html | title=Woman in Crimea escaped from hospital before checking for coronavirus}}</ref>\n\nOn 2 March, the first case of coronavirus in [[Moscow]] was confirmed.<ref name=moscow.1>{{cite web|url=https://www.interfax.ru/russia/697390|title=\u0423 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0435\u0445\u0430\u0432\u0448\u0435\u0433\u043e \u0438\u0437 \u0418\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0438 \u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u044f\u043d\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u043e\u0431\u043d\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0436\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441|website=Interfax.ru}}</ref><ref name=\"rusmar2\" /> A young man fell ill on 21 February while on holiday in [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy|Italy]], and returned to Russia on 23 February, staying at his house in [[Moscow Oblast]].<ref name=moscow.1 /> He showed up with symptoms at a clinic on 27 February, and was then hospitalised in Moscow.<ref name=moscow.1 /> He was reported to be recovered on 6 March.<ref name=\"rusmar6-rec\" />\n\nOn 5 March, the first case of coronavirus in [[Saint Petersburg]] was confirmed. An Italian student returned to Russia from Italy on 29 February, was hospitalised on 2 March and recovered on 13 March.<ref name=\"rusmar5\" /><ref name=\"rusmar13-rec\" />\n\nOn 6 March, six more cases were confirmed, with five of them being in Moscow and one of them being in [[Nizhny Novgorod]]. All of them are reported to be linked to Italy.<ref name=\"rusmar6\" />\n\nOn 7 March, four cases were confirmed, three in [[Lipetsk]] and one in [[Saint Petersburg]]. All of them have returned from Italy.<ref name=\"rusmar7\" />\n\nOn 8 March, three new cases in [[Belgorod Oblast|Belgorod]], [[Moscow Oblast|Moscow]] and [[Kaliningrad Oblast|Kaliningrad]] oblasts were confirmed, all of them have returned from Italy.<ref name=\"rusmar8\" />\n\nOn 9 March, three cases in Moscow were confirmed, all of them coming from Italy.<ref name=\"rusmar9\" />\n\nOn 11 March, eight new cases were confirmed, six in Moscow and two in [[Moscow Oblast]], all people coming from Italy.<ref name=\"rusmar11\" />\n\nOn 12 March, six cases were confirmed, including four in Moscow, one in [[Kaliningrad Oblast]] and the first case in [[Krasnodar Krai]].<ref name=\"rusmar12\" /> On the same day, two tourists arrived from Moscow on 3 March were diagnosed with the disease in Israel.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.kommersant.ru/doc/4285509|title=\u0412 \u0418\u0437\u0440\u0430\u0438\u043b\u0435 \u0432\u044b\u044f\u0432\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0443 \u0434\u0432\u0443\u0445 \u0442\u0443\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u0438\u0437 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u044b|newspaper=Kommersant|language=ru|trans-title=Two tourists from Moscow revealed coronavirus in Israel|date=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 March, 11 new cases were confirmed: five in Moscow, three in St. Petersburg, one in [[Leningrad Oblast]], Moscow Oblast, and [[Perm Krai]]. All of the patients came from Italy, [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in France|France]], or [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Austria|Austria]], except for one who got infected locally.<ref name=\"rusmar13\" />\n\nOn 14 March, first two cases in [[Kemerovo Oblast]] were confirmed. Also, there were nine new cases in Moscow, one in Moscow Oblast, Saint Petersburg and Kaliningrad Oblast each.<ref name=\"rusmar14\" />\n\nOn 15 March, four new cases were confirmed, including three in Moscow region and one in Tyumen. The patients had recently visited Spain, Italy, France and Switzerland.<ref name=\"rusmar15\"/>\n\nOn 16 March, 30 new cases were confirmed, bringing the total number of cases to 93. Deputy Prime Minister [[Tatyana Golikova]] announced that 7 cases were from contact with other patients while the other 86 were imported.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u0427\u0438\u0441\u043b\u043e \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0438\u0432\u0448\u0438\u0445\u0441\u044f \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c \u0432 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u0432\u043e\u0437\u0440\u043e\u0441\u043b\u043e \u0434\u043e 93|url=https://tass.ru/obschestvo/7991927|agency=[[TASS]]|date=16 March 2020}}</ref> 3 new cases were in [[Samara Oblast]] for the first time, with the first cases in [[Kirov Oblast]] and [[Komi Republic]].<ref name=\"rusmar16\"/>\n\nOn 17 March, 21 more cases were confirmed; four in Moscow, two in Samara Oblast, Kaliningrad Oblast, [[Tver Oblast]], one in Moscow Oblast, [[Krasnoyarsk Krai]], [[Tambov Oblast]], [[Kaluga Oblast]], Nizhny Novgorod Oblast, [[Penza Oblast]], [[Tatarstan]], [[Khakassia]], [[Sverdlovsk Oblast]], [[Arkhangelsk Oblast]], [[Yaroslavl Oblast]].<ref name=\"rusmar17\" /> One patient got cured.<ref name=\"Rus_Ministry\" />\n\nOn 18 March, 33 new cases were confirmed including 31 in Moscow, one new case in [[Novosibirsk Oblast]] and [[Tomsk Oblast]] each.<ref name=\"rusmar18\" />\n\nOn 19 March, the first death of a patient with confirmed COVID-19 was reported in Moscow. A 79-year-old woman was first hospitalised on 13 March and transferred to a private clinic the next day. Upon confirmation of COVID-19 she was transferred to an intensive care ward in Moscow Infectious Hospital #2. She also suffered from [[type 2 diabetes]], [[hypertension]], [[coronary artery disease]] (and underwent [[coronary stenting]]), coronary and aortic [[atherosclerosis]], chronic [[pulmonary hypertension]], [[kidney stone disease]], and [[cerebrovascular disease]].<ref name=\"Rus_1stdeath_TASS\">{{cite news |title=Elderly woman with coronavirus dies in Moscow\n |url=https://tass.com/society/1132327 |accessdate=19 March 2020 |agency=TASS |date=19 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=\u0428\u0442\u0430\u0431: \u0423\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0448\u0430\u044f \u0432 \u0431\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u0436\u0438\u043b\u0430\u044f \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043a\u0430 \u0438\u043c\u0435\u043b\u0430 \u0446\u0435\u043b\u044b\u0439 \u0440\u044f\u0434 \u0441\u0435\u0440\u044c\u0435\u0437\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0445\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0445 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0439 |url=https://www.mskagency.ru/materials/2984079 |accessdate=19 March 2020 |agency=AGN \"Moscow\" |date=19 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref> However, [[pulmonary embolism]] was identified as the direct cause of her death,<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u043e\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u043e\u043c \u0448\u0442\u0430\u0431\u0435 \u043d\u0430\u0437\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0443 \u0441\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0442\u0438 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043a\u0438 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c \u0432 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0435 |url=https://tass.ru/obschestvo/8025791 |accessdate=19 March 2020 |agency=TASS |date=19 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref> she had no pathological changes in lungs,<ref>{{cite news |title=\u041d\u0430\u0437\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0442\u0438 \u043c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0438\u0447\u043a\u0438 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c |url=https://ria.ru/20200319/1568838480.html |accessdate=19 March 2020 |agency=RIA Novosti |date=19 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref> and her death was not officially counted as caused by coronavirus.<ref name=\"rusmar19\" /><ref name=\"RBC\">{{cite news |title=\u041e\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0448\u0442\u0430\u0431 \u0437\u0430\u044f\u0432\u0438\u043b \u043e\u0431 \u043e\u0442\u0441\u0443\u0442\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0438\u0438 \u0432 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u043b\u0435\u0442\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0438\u0441\u0445\u043e\u0434\u043e\u0432 \u043e\u0442 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 |url=https://www.rbc.ru/rbcfreenews/5e736ddf9a7947c662f701ed |accessdate=19 March 2020 |work=RBC |date=19 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref> The victim was identified in the media as Valentina Zubareva, professor at the [[Gubkin Russian State University of Oil and Gas|Gubkin University]], she had contracted the disease in Russia.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0423\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0448\u0430\u044f \u043e\u0442 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u043f\u043e\u0434\u0430\u0432\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0430 \u0413\u0443\u0431\u043a\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0443\u043d\u0438\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u0442\u0435\u0442\u0430 \u043c\u043e\u0433\u043b\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0438\u0442\u044c\u0441\u044f \u043e\u0442 \u0432\u043d\u0443\u0447\u043a\u0438 |url=https://dailystorm.ru/news/umershaya-ot-koronavirusa-prepodavatelnica-gubkinskogo-universiteta-mogla-zarazitsya-ot-vnuchki |website=Daily Storm |accessdate=19 March 2020 |language=ru |date=19 March 2020}}</ref> 52 new cases were also confirmed in 23 regions including first cases in [[Chuvashia]], [[Yakutia]], [[Khabarovsk Krai]], [[Ivanovo Oblast|Ivanovo]], [[Murmansk Oblast|Murmansk]], [[Orenburg Oblast|Orenburg]], [[Ryazan Oblast|Ryazan]], [[Saratov Oblast|Saratov]], [[Tula Oblast|Tula]], [[Voronezh Oblast|Voronezh]] oblasts, and [[Khanty-Mansi Autonomous Okrug]], bringing the total number to 199.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://tass.ru/obschestvo/8027139|title=\u0427\u0438\u0441\u043b\u043e \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0438\u0432\u0448\u0438\u0445\u0441\u044f \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c \u0432 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u0432\u044b\u0440\u043e\u0441\u043b\u043e \u0434\u043e 199|agency=[[TASS]]|date=19 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"rusmar19\" />\n\nOn 20 March, 54 new cases were confirmed, including 33 in Moscow, 6 in Yakutia, 4 in Saint Petersburg, 4 in Samara Oblast, 2 in Kirov Oblast, 2 in Novosibirsk Oblast, 1 in Moscow Oblast, 1 in Tyumen Oblast, and the first case in [[Ulyanovsk Oblast]].<ref name=\"rusmar20\" />\n\nOn 21 March, 53 new cases were confirmed in 18 federal subjects, including first cases in [[Kabardino-Balkaria]] (2 cases), [[Stavropol Krai]], [[Chelyabinsk Oblast]], [[Kurgan Oblast]], and disputed [[Republic of Crimea]] (1 case each).<ref name=\"rusmar21\" />\n\nOn 22 March, 61 new cases were confirmed, including 54 in Moscow, 2 in Kirov Oblast, 1 case in Arkhangelsk Oblast, first cases in [[Udmurtia]] (2 cases), [[Bryansk Oblast]], and [[Novgorod Oblast]] (1 case each).<ref name=\"rusmar22\" />\n\nOn 23 March, 71 new cases were confirmed, all of them in Moscow.<ref name=\"rusmar23\"/>\n\nOn 24 March, 57 new cases were confirmed, including first cases in [[Primorsky Krai]], [[Oryol Oblast]], the [[Chechen Republic]], [[Volgograd Oblast]] and [[Bashkortostan]].<ref name=\"rusmar24\"/>\n\nOn 25 March, 163 new cases were confirmed, 120 of them in Moscow, with first cases in [[Pskov Oblast]] and [[Rostov Oblast]].<ref name=\"rusmar25\"/> 2 deaths were also later reported and confirmed in Moscow. The patients were 73 and 88 years old and had been tested positive for the coronavirus.<ref name=\"tass-deaths-mar25\">{{cite news|url=https://tass.ru/obschestvo/8077753|title=\u0412 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0435 \u0443\u043c\u0435\u0440\u043b\u0438 \u0434\u0432\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0436\u0438\u043b\u044b\u0445 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0430 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c|agency=[[TASS]]|date=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 March, 182 new cases were confirmed, 136 of them in Moscow, with first cases in [[Buryatia]].<ref name=\"rusmar26\"/> According to a source in the hospital and an official report to the prosecutor office, a 83-year-old woman (a patient of a surgeon who got sick earlier, see 31 March) died in [[Syktyvkar]] of COVID-19, the death was covered up by the local authorities and not included in the official count.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://novayagazeta.ru/news/2020/03/26/160141-istochnik-v-syktyvkare-umerla-pozhilaya-patsientka-s-podtverzhdennym-koronavirusom |title=\u0418\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0447\u043d\u0438\u043a: \u0432 \u0421\u044b\u043a\u0442\u044b\u0432\u043a\u0430\u0440\u0435 \u0443\u043c\u0435\u0440\u043b\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0436\u0438\u043b\u0430\u044f \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043a\u0430 \u0441 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0436\u0434\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u043c \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c |publisher=Novayagazeta.ru |date= |accessdate=2020-04-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.severreal.org/a/30511036.html |title = \u041a\u043e\u043c\u0438: \u043e\u0442 \u043f\u043d\u0435\u0432\u043c\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0438 \u0441\u043a\u043e\u043d\u0447\u0430\u043b\u0430\u0441\u044c \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043a\u0430, \u0443 \u043a\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0439 \u0431\u044b\u043b \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441}}</ref> An official working under the chief of staff of the prime minister also tested positive for the coronavirus that day.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://meduza.io/news/2020/03/26/u-odnogo-iz-sotrudnikov-apparata-pravitelstva-rf-obnaruzhili-koronavirus|title=\u0423 \u0441\u043e\u0442\u0440\u0443\u0434\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u0430\u043f\u043f\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 \u0420\u0424 \u043d\u0430\u0448\u043b\u0438 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441. \"\u0420\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u0430 \u0411\u0438-\u0431\u0438-\u0441\u0438\" \u0441\u043e\u043e\u0431\u0449\u0438\u043b\u0430 \u043e \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0430\u043a\u0430\u0445 \u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0443 \u0442\u0440\u0435\u0445 \u0435\u0433\u043e \u043a\u043e\u043b\u043b\u0435\u0433|website=[[Meduza]]|date=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 March, 196 new cases were confirmed, 157 of them in Moscow, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 1,036. First cases in [[Mordovia]] and [[Dagestan]] were confirmed. An additional death in Moscow, a 70-year-old woman with pre-existing conditions who tested positive for coronavirus, was also confirmed.<ref name=\"rusmar27\"/> On the same day, the Kremlin confirmed that an employee of the [[Russian presidential administration|presidential administration]] tested positive for the coronavirus, saying that the official had no contact with the president.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2020/03/27/kremlin-confirms-first-coronavirus-infection-in-putins-administration-a69780|title=Kremlin Confirms First Coronavirus Infection in Putin's Administration|website=[[The Moscow Times]]|date=27 March 2020}}</ref> Russian singer [[Lev Leshchenko]] was also confirmed to have tested positive for the virus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2020/03/27/renowned-soviet-singer-lev-leshchenko-tests-positive-for-coronavirus-a69773|title=Renowned Soviet Singer Lev Leshchenko Tests Positive for Coronavirus|date=27 March 2020|website=[[The Moscow Times]]}}</ref> Later in the day, the 4th death was reported, a 56-year-old woman with one lung due to cancer, also in Moscow.<ref>{{cite news|URL=https://www.interfax.ru/moscow/701306|title=\u0427\u0435\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0442\u044b\u0439 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442 \u0441 COVID-19 \u0441\u043a\u043e\u043d\u0447\u0430\u043b\u0441\u044f \u0432 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0435|agency=[[Interfax]]|date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 March, the fifth patient died in [[Orenburg]], the first death outside of Moscow. The 57-year-old man from [[Buzuluk, Orenburg Oblast|Buzuluk]], Orenburg Oblast was travelling in [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in France|France]], [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Spain|Spain]] and [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Turkey|Turkey]] in March. He had a chronic pathology.<ref name=\n\"5th-death\">{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u041e\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0435 \u0441\u043a\u043e\u043d\u0447\u0430\u043b\u0441\u044f \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c |url=https://www.interfax.ru/russia/701345 |accessdate=28 March 2020 |work=[[Interfax]] |date=28 March 2020}}</ref> 228 new cases were confirmed, 114 of them in Moscow, bringing the total number of cases to 1,264. First cases were confirmed in [[Adygea]], [[Kostroma Oblast|Kostroma]], [[Sakhalin Oblast|Sakhalin]] and [[Smolensk Oblast|Smolensk]] oblasts.<ref name=\"rusmar28\"/> Later that day, two deaths were reported in Saint Petersburg and Moscow.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u041f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0435 \u0443\u043c\u0435\u0440 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c |url=https://tass.ru/obschestvo/8105635 |accessdate=28 March 2020 |work=[[TASS]] |date=28 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0435 \u0443\u043c\u0435\u0440 \u043f\u044f\u0442\u044b\u0439 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c |url=https://tass.ru/obschestvo/8105925 |accessdate=28 March 2020 |work=[[TASS]] |date=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 29 March, 270 new cases were confirmed, 197 of them in Moscow, bringing the total number in the city to 1,014 and in the country to 1,534. Mayor of Moscow [[Sergey Sobyanin]] later in the day announced that the city would be on lockdown starting the next day.<ref name=\"tmt-mar29\">{{cite web|url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2020/03/29/moscow-orders-citywide-quarantine-starting-march-30-a69789|title=Moscow Orders Citywide Quarantine Starting March 30|website=[[The Moscow Times]]|date = 29 March 2020}}</ref> [[Irkutsk Oblast]], [[Amur Oblast]] and [[Omsk Oblast]] all had their first confirmed cases. The total number of confirmed deaths reached 8.<ref name=\"rusmar29\"/>\n\nOn 30 March, 302 new cases were confirmed, including 212 in Moscow, bringing the total number to 1,836. First cases were found in [[Kalmykia]], [[Mari El]], [[Altai Krai]], [[Vladimir Oblast]], and [[Vologda Oblast]]. The number of deaths rose to 9.<ref name=\"rusmar30\"/>\n\nOn 31 March, 500 new cases were confirmed, 387 of them in Moscow and 48 of them in St. Petersburg, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 2,337 in the 7th consecutive one-day record. First cases in [[Magadan Oblast]] and [[Astrakhan Oblast]] were confirmed that day. The number of confirmed deaths almost doubled from 9 the previous day to 17.<ref name=\"rusmar31\"/> The medical director of Moscow's main coronavirus hospital in [[Kommunarka]], Denis Protsenko, was also reported to have tested positive for the coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2020/03/31/russias-top-coronavirus-doctor-tests-positive-media-a69815|title=\nRussia's Top Coronavirus Doctor Tests Positive \u2013 Media|website=[[The Moscow Times]]|date=31 March 2020}}</ref> A 61-year-old female, manager of the Syktyvkar hospital, which became a focus of the disease after a surgeon got sick on March 16th, died of COVID-19, but again, as with the death of a patient of the hospital surgical department on March 26th (see above), the death wasn't included in the official statistic even despite the pathology lab officially confirmed the diagnosis to the local media.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://7x7-journal.ru/news/2020/04/01/v-komi-skonchalas-zavhoz-bolnicy-gde-bolee-50-chelovek-zarazilos-koronavirusom |title=\u0412 \u041a\u043e\u043c\u0438 \u0441\u043a\u043e\u043d\u0447\u0430\u043b\u0430\u0441\u044c \u0437\u0430\u0432\u0445\u043e\u0437 \u0431\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u0446\u044b, \u0433\u0434\u0435 \u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0435 50 \u0447\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043a \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0438\u043b\u043e\u0441\u044c \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c |publisher=7x7-journal.ru |date= |accessdate=2020-04-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://meduza.io/feature/2020/04/01/respublika-komi-vyshla-v-lidery-po-chislu-zarazhennyh-koronavirusom-v-rasprostranenii-infektsii-zapodozrili-vracha |title=\u0420\u0435\u0441\u043f\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u041a\u043e\u043c\u0438 \u0432\u044b\u0448\u043b\u0430 \u0432 \u043b\u0438\u0434\u0435\u0440\u044b \u043f\u043e \u0447\u0438\u0441\u043b\u0443 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c. \u0412 \u0440\u0430\u0441\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0438 \u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u043f\u043e\u0434\u043e\u0437\u0440\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u0432\u0440\u0430\u0447\u0430 \u2014 Meduza |publisher=Meduza.io |date= |accessdate=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n\nOn 1 April, 440 new cases were confirmed, less than the number of new cases in the previous day, with 267 of them in Moscow, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 2,777. First cases were confirmed in [[Kursk Oblast]] and [[North Ossetia]]. The number of confirmed deaths rose by 7 to 24.<ref name=\"rusapr1\"/>\n\nOn 2 April, 771 new cases were confirmed, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 3,548. The number of confirmed deaths rose by 8 to 30.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rospotrebnadzor.ru/about/info/news/news_details.php?ELEMENT_ID=14160|title=\u041e \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0436\u0434\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u044f\u0445 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u0438 COVID-2019 \u0432 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 02.04.2020|website=Rospotrebnadzor|date = 2 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 3 April, 601 new cases were confirmed, less than the number of new cases in the previous day, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 4,149. The number of confirmed deaths rose by 4 to 34.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rospotrebnadzor.ru/about/info/news/news_details.php?ELEMENT_ID=14171|title=\u041e \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0436\u0434\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u044f\u0445 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u0438 COVID-2019 \u0432 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 03.04.2020|website=Rospotrebnadzor|date = 3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Statistics ==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Russia medical cases chart}}\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Russia medical cases}}\n\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type=line\n|linewidth=1\n|showSymbols=1\n|width=680\n|colors=#FF6347,#FFC000,#87CEEB,#000000\n|showValues=\n|xAxisTitle=Date\n|xAxisAngle=-40\n|x=31 Jan, ..., 11 Feb, 12 Feb, ...., 2 Mar, ....., 5 Mar, 6 Mar, 7 Mar, 8 Mar, 9 Mar, 10 Mar, 11 Mar, 12 Mar, 13 Mar, 14 Mar, 15 Mar, 16 Mar, 17 Mar, 18 Mar