untries by hospital beds|Extracorporeal membrane oxygenation#The number of ECMOs by countries and territories}}\n\nOn March 19, 2020, the Russian Government reported the following data. More than 55 thousand infectious beds were deployed, including more than 12 thousand intensive care units and 396 observatories. 7.5 thousand Melzer boxes were prepared. Medical organizations have more than 40 thousand devices for artificial lung ventilation, 124 devices for extracorporeal membrane oxygenation (ECMO). The government of the Russian Federation has allocated resources for the additional purchase of more than 500 devices, including 17 ECMO devices. Today, 6 thousand infectious diseases doctors and almost 2 thousand pulmonologists, more than 18 thousand nurses are ready to provide medical assistance.<ref>http://government.ru/news/39218/</ref>\n\nThe independent journalistic website [[proekt.media]] reports that as soon as the number of cases of coronavirus in Russia reaches 800 thousand people, and the number of hospitalized \u2014 160 thousand, ventilation devices in hospitals will run out.<br/>According to the [[OECD]], Russia ranks third in the number of beds per capita. However, in the case of Russia, beds are literally only beds. In terms of equipment \u2014 for example, CT and MRI devices \u2014 Russia is in 28th place with a dramatic gap from the leaders. [[Rosstat]] does not publish data on the number of places in intensive care units and equipment. In total, there are 1 million 172 thousand beds in Russian hospitals, according to Rosstat data for 2018. These include intensive care units. Intensive care bed means a bed equipped with a set of equipment for resuscitation and intensive care, including ventilators. The Institute of Phthisiopulmonology and infectious diseases of the Ministry of health estimated the number of intensive care beds at just 12 thousand, which is three times less than the Ministry of health's standard. The proekt.media website was able to find data on the number of intensive care beds in only 23 regions. Only Moscow, Kalmykia, Altai and Komi reached the standard of 3%. Other regions are significantly below the standard.<br/>Separate ventilators in hospitals should be more than intensive care beds. The number of ventilators in a region should be at least 1.5 times more than the number of intensive care beds. There are no official statistics on the number of ventilators. Federal authorities with the beginning of the epidemic conducted their own calculations: Deputy Prime Minister [[Tatyana Golikova]] said that Russia has 40 thousand ventilators. This is 3.4% of the total number of beds in Russia, and more than 12 thousand devices are missing from the standards of the Ministry of health. This is a total deficit of 23%, but in some regions it is much larger.\n<ref>https://www.proekt.media/research/koronavirus-regiony/</ref>\n\nData collected by the news website [[Meduza]] indicates that Russia's supply of ventilators is quite extensive: Even the number available per capita in some geographically peripheral regions, not to mention Moscow, significantly exceeds ventilator supplies in Western countries. That said, ventilators alone are not enough to overcome the pandemic. Without a specialist nearby, rental ventilators will be useless. In a number of other areas, comparing Russian and Italian health infrastructure doesn't bode well at all for Russia.<br/>Aside from the question of whether the ventilators available actually fit patients\u2019 needs, there's the fact that if a patient has to be on a ventilator, they're already in critical condition. That means they need a whole set of critical care procedures, specialized equipment, and medical professionals who can use that equipment and put those measures in place. This is where Russian medicine loses out to Italy. For example, when Italy says they don't have enough nurses, for them, that means there used to be one nurse per patient, and now, there's one for every two. Well, we\u2019ve got one nurse serving three or four or five already.<ref>https://meduza.io/en/feature/2020/03/21/the-ventilator-problem</ref>\n{{Collapse top}}\n{{Bar chart\n| title       = VENTILATORS PER 100,000 RESIDENTS\n| label_type  = REGION\n| data_type   = VENTILATORS PER 100,000 RESIDENTS\n| bar_width   = 50\n| width_units = em\n| data_max    = 57\n\n| label1   = \nKhanty-Mansi AO\n| data1    = \n56.8\n\n| label2   = \nSamara region\n| data2    = \n42.6\n\n| label3   = \nAmur region\n| data3    = \n42.5\n\n| label4   = \nMoscow (city)\n| data4    = \n40\n\n| label5   = \nKirov region\n| data5    = \n39.6\n\n| label6   = \nArkhangelsk region\n| data6    = \n38.4\n\n| label7   = \nSakha Republic (Yakutia)\n| data7    = \n37.2\n\n| label8   = \nSakhalin region\n| data8    = \n37.1\n\n| label9   = \nTomsk region\n| data9    = \n37.1\n\n| label10   = \nSt. Petersburg (city)\n| data10    = \n35.2\n\n| label11   = \nLipetsk region\n| data11    = \n35.1\n\n| label12   = \nSverdlovsk region\n| data12    = \n35\n\n| label13   = \nChuvash Republic (Chuvashia)\n| data13    = \n34.7\n\n| label14   = \nAltai Krai\n| data14    = \n34.6\n\n| label15   = \nRepublic of Crimea (status disputed)\n| data15    = \n34.3\n\n| label16   = \nRepublic of Karelia\n| data16    = \n32.5\n\n| label17   = \nYaroslavl region\n| data17    = \n31.5\n\n| label18   = \nVladimir region\n| data18    = \n31.4\n\n| label19   = \nTambov region\n| data19    = \n31.2\n| label20   = \nPenza region\n| data20    = \n30.7\n\n| label21   = \nMurmansk region\n| data21    = \n30.5\n\n| label22   = \nPskov region\n| data22    = \n30.3\n\n| label23   = \nRepublic of Tatarstan\n| data23    = \n28.2\n| label24   = \nOrenburg region\n| data24    = \n27.7\n\n| label25   = \n'''Russia'''\n| data25    = \n27.3\n\n| label26   = \nKemerovo region\n| data26    = \n27.3\n\n| label27   = \nRyazan region\n| data27    = \n27.1\n\n| label28   = \nIrkutsk region\n| data28    = \n26.5\n\n| label29   = \nRepublic of Bashkortostan (Bashkiria)\n| data29    = \n25.5\n\n| label30   = \nRepublic of Buryatia\n| data30    = \n24.9\n\n}}\n\n{{Bar chart\n| title       = VENTILATORS PER 100,000 RESIDENTS\n| label_type  = REGION\n| data_type   = VENTILATORS PER 100,000 RESIDENTS\n| bar_width   = 50\n| width_units = em\n| data_max    = 57\n\n| label1   = \nKrasnoyarsk Krai\n| data1    = \n24.6\n\n| label2   = \nChelyabinsk region\n| data2    = \n24.5\n\n| label3   = \nAstrakhan region\n| data3    = \n23.9\n\n| label4   = \nZabaikalsky Krai\n| data4    = \n22.8\n\n| label5   = \nSaratov region\n| data5    = \n22.1\n\n| label6   = \nVologda region\n| data6    = \n22.1\n\n| label7   = \nKursk region\n| data7    = \n21.9\n\n| label8   = \nOrel region\n| data8    = \n21.8\n\n| label9   = \nMari El Republic\n| data9    = \n20.9\n\n| label10   = \nNovosibirsk region\n| data10    = \n20.4\n\n| label11   = \nTula region\n| data11    = \n20.3\n\n| label12   = \nUdmurt Republic (Udmurtia)\n| data12    = \n20.2\n\n| label13   = \nPerm Krai\n| data13    = \n20\n\n| label14   = \nKostroma region\n| data14    = \n19.1\n\n| label15   = \n'''United States'''\n| data15    = \n18.8\n\n| label16   = \nKaliningrad region\n| data16    = \n18.8\n\n| label17   = \nOmsk region\n| data17    = \n18.7\n\n| label18   = \nIvanovo region\n| data18    = \n17.9\n\n| label19   = \nKrasnodar Krai\n| data19    = \n17.6\n\n| label20   = \nBelgorod region\n| data20    = \n16.8\n\n| label21   = \nRostov region\n| data21    = \n15.3\n\n| label22   = \nVoronezh region\n| data22    = \n15\n\n| label23   = \nLeningrad region\n| data23    = \n14.3\n\n| label24   = \n'''United Kingdom'''\n| data24    = \n12.9\n\n| label25   = \nSevastopol (city; status disputed)\n| data25    = \n12.9\n\n| label26   = \nTver region\n| data26    = \n9.4\n\n| label27   = \n'''Ukraine'''\n| data27    = \n8.6\n\n| label28   = \n'''Italy'''\n| data28    = \n8.3\n\n| label29   = \nKaluga region\n| data29    = \n4.8\n\n}}\n{{Collapse bottom}}\n\n== Government responses ==\n{{multiple image\n | align = right\n |direction = vertical\n | total_width = 250\n | image1 = \u0421\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0449\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043e \u043c\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0445 \u043f\u043e \u0431\u043e\u0440\u044c\u0431\u0435 \u0441 \u0440\u0430\u0441\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435\u043c \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 \u0432 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 (\u0412. \u041f\u0443\u0442\u0438\u043d).jpg\n | alt1 = \n | caption1 = On 29 January, Russian President [[Vladimir Putin]] held a meeting on measures to counter the spread of coronavirus in Russia.<ref>[http://en.kremlin.ru/events/president/news/62691 Meeting on measures to counter the spread of coronavirus in Russia]</ref>\n | image2 = State Council on countering the spread of coronavirus1.jpg\n | caption2 = On 16 March, Mayor of Moscow [[Sergei Sobyanin]] held the first meeting of the State Council working group on countering the spread of coronavirus.\n | footer = \n}}\n\nRussia implemented preventive measures to curb the spread of COVID-19 in the country by imposing quarantines, carrying raids on potential virus carriers and using facial recognition to impose quarantine measures.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-moscow-deportation-idUSKCN20M252|title=Russia to deport 88 foreigners for violating coronavirus quarantine|date=28 February 2020|work=Reuters|access-date=29 February 2020|language=en}}</ref> Measures to prevent a crisis in Russia include banning the export of medical masks, random checks on the [[Moscow Metro]], and cancellation of large-scale events by schools. The Russian government has also taken measures to prevent foreign citizens from heavily affected countries from visiting Russia.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web |title=Protect Putin from Covid-19: Kremlin's new mission as epidemic spreads worldwide |url=https://www.rt.com/russia/482289-protect-putin-from-covid/ |accessdate=5 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe Russian consumer health watchdog [[Rospotrebnadzor]] advised tourists to refrain from visiting Wuhan and stay away from Chinese zoos and markets selling animals and seafood. The agency also said that development of a vaccine against the virus was underway, relying on the WHO's recommendations.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2020/01/22/russian-tourists-undeterred-from-china-despite-coronavirus-outbreak-a69007|title=Russian Tourists Undeterred From China Despite coronavirus pandemic|accessdate=25 January 2020|date=22 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/china-health-russia-vaccine/russia-is-developing-vaccine-against-coronavirus-ria-cites-regulator-idUSR4N29M01K|title=Russia is developing vaccine against coronavirus \u2013 RIA cites regulator|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200123012316/https://www.reuters.com/article/china-health-russia-vaccine/russia-is-developing-vaccine-against-coronavirus-ria-cites-regulator-idUSR4N29M01K|archive-date=23 January 2020|accessdate=25 January 2020|agency=Reuters|date=22 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n144 Russians were evacuated from [[Wuhan]], the initial centre of the outbreak, and were quarantined in [[Tyumen Oblast]] for two weeks from 5 February.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russians Start 2-Week Coronavirus Quarantine After Return From Wuhan |url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2020/02/05/russians-start-2-week-coronavirus-quarantine-after-return-from-wuhan-a69155 |accessdate=9 March 2020 |work=[[The Moscow Times]] |date=5 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 4 March, Russia temporarily banned the export of medical masks, gloves, bandages and protective suits.<ref name=\"mwt\" />\n\nOn 21 March, it was announced that Russia delivered over 100,000 test kits to 13 countries, including Armenia, Belarus, Kyrgyzstan, Uzbekistan, Serbia, Egypt, Venezuela, Iran, and North Korea.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russia delivers over 100,000 Covid-19 test kits to 13 states, including Iran, North Korea |url=https://www.rt.com/russia/483701-russia-ships-coronavirus-testing/ |accessdate=21 March 2020 |work=[[RT (TV network)|RT]] |date=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 March, after a phone call with [[Italy|Italian]] Prime Minister [[Giuseppe Conte]], Russian president [[Vladimir Putin]] arranged the Russian army to send medical help to Italy, which was the European country hardest hit by coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russian army to send coronavirus help to Italy after Putin phone call |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-russia-italy/russian-army-to-send-coronavirus-help-to-italy-after-putin-phone-call-idUSKBN219081 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=Reuters |date=22 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, [[Moscow Mayor]] [[Sergey Sobyanin]] told President Putin at a meeting that \"a serious situation is unfolding\" and that the relatively low number of confirmed cases could be due to a low level of testing, saying that \"there are far more people who are infected\" and that the number of people in Moscow suspected of having the coronavirus was about 500.<ref name=\"sobyanin-mar24\">{{cite web|url=https://meduza.io/en/news/2020/03/24/moscow-s-mayor-warns-putin-that-regional-officials-don-t-understand-coronavirus-risks-and-says-low-levels-of-testing-could-explain-russia-s-small-number-of-confirmed-cases|title=Moscow's mayor warns Putin that regional officials don't understand coronavirus risks and says low levels of testing could explain Russia's small number of confirmed cases|website=[[Meduza]]|date=24 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://tass.com/society/1134701|title=No real picture of COVID-2019 situation in Russian regions \u2014 Moscow mayor|agency=[[TASS]]|date=24 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://tass.com/society/1134671|title=About 500 people in Moscow suspected of having COVID|agency=[[TASS]]|date=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Testing ===\n\nAs of 23 March, [[Russia]] has 4 testing systems and has carried out over 165 thousand tests for the coronavirus<ref name=\"test\">{{cite web |title=\u041e\u0431 \u0438\u0437\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0438 \u0441\u0445\u0435\u043c\u044b \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0436\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043f\u043e\u0434\u043e\u0437\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043d\u0443\u044e \u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u044e \u0440\u0435\u0437\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u0438\u0441\u0441\u043b\u0435\u0434\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0439 |url=https://rospotrebnadzor.ru/about/info/news/news_details.php?ELEMENT_ID=14090 |publisher=[[Rospotrebnadzor]] |accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Over 163,000 coronavirus tests carried out in Russia\">{{cite news |title=Over 163,000 coronavirus tests carried out in Russia |url=https://tass.com/society/1133655 |accessdate=23 March 2020 |work=RUSSIAN NEWS AGENCY |language=en}}</ref> which is among the highest testing numbers in the world.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://ourworldindata.org/covid-testing |title = How many tests for COVID-19 are being performed around the world?}}</ref> Two private lab companies started testing on 26 March. According to Deputy Prime Minister [[Tatyana Golikova]], as of 25 March, 141 state laboratories were conducting tests in 79 federal subjects.<ref>{{cite news |title=Two Russian private labs launch coronavirus testing |url=https://tass.com/economy/1135125 |accessdate=26 March 2020 |work=[[TASS]] |date=25 March 2020}}</ref> There are plans to increase the number of reference centres across the country to 15.<ref name=\"mwt\"/><ref name=\"test\" /><ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0435 \u0431\u0443\u0434\u0443\u0442 \u0434\u0438\u0430\u0433\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0442\u044c COVID-19 \u0431\u0435\u0437 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0438 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u0438\u0447\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0442\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0430 \u0432 \u041d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0441\u0438\u0431\u0438\u0440\u0441\u043a\u0435 |url=https://www.interfax.ru/russia/700428 |accessdate=23 March 2020 |work=[[Interfax]] |date=23 March 2020}}</ref> On 27 March, the [[Federal Service for Surveillance in Healthcare]] (Roszdravnadzor) registered two more test systems.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0435\u0433\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u044b \u0434\u0432\u0430 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0445 \u0442\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 |url=https://meduza.io/news/2020/03/30/v-rossii-zaregistrirovany-dva-novyh-testa-na-koronavirus |accessdate=30 March 2020 |work=[[Meduza]] |date=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nDr. Melita Vujnovic, the [[World Health Organization]]'s representative in Russia, stated that Russia, in accordance with WHO recommendations, \"started testing literally at the end of January.\u201d<ref name=\"Why does Russia, population 146 million, have fewer coronavirus cases than Luxembourg?, CNN\">{{cite news |title= Why does Russia, population 146 million, have fewer coronavirus cases than Luxembourg? |url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/21/europe/putin-coronavirus-russia-intl/index.html |accessdate=23 March 2020 |work=CNN |language=en}}</ref> Coronavirus testing in Russia was provided by the [[State Research Center of Virology and Biotechnology VECTOR]] in [[Novosibirsk]] and had to be verified there.<ref name=\"CNN Why\"/><ref name=\"NBC Russia's low infection\"/> There was concern that the tests may have insufficient sensitivity,<ref name=\"CNN Why\"/><ref name=\"NBC Russia's low infection\"/> despite the fact that the tests were verified in China since early February, showed the degree of sensitivity similar to or higher than other tests and the lab has been approved by the [[World Health Organization]].<ref name=\"CNN Why\"/> Since 23 March, [[European Russia]] doesn't send their batches to Novosibirsk for verification but verify them in a Moscow reference centre.\n\nThere was some skepticism about the accuracy of Russia's reported infection figures. Anastasia Vasilyeva, leader of the Doctors' Alliance organisation loosely aligned to the Russian opposition and doctor for opposition figure [[Alexei Navalny]], made a series of videos accusing the authorities of concealing the true number of coronavirus cases by using pneumonia and acute respiratory infection as a diagnosis instead. Health officials rejected the allegation, and President Putin addressed concerns about statistics, saying that the government is not covering up the number of cases, though might not have the full picture. The [[World Health Organization|WHO's]] representative to Russia, Dr. Vujnovic, also expressed skepticism at the allegation.<ref name=\"CNN Why\">{{cite news |last1=CNN |first1=Mary Ilyushina |title=Why does Russia, population 146 million, have fewer coronavirus cases than Luxembourg? |url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/21/europe/putin-coronavirus-russia-intl/index.html |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=CNN}}</ref><ref name=\"NBC Russia's low infection\">{{cite news |title=Russia's low infection numbers viewed skeptically |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/coronavirus-russia-s-low-infection-numbers-viewed-skeptically-n1166101 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=NBC News |language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"sobyanin-mar24\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2020/03/27/russias-coronavirus-cases-surpass-1000-in-biggest-one-day-jump-a69710|title=Russia's Coronavirus Cases Surpass 1,000 in Biggest One-Day Jump|website=[[The Moscow Times]]|date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Travel and entry restrictions ===\n[[File:COVID-19 pandemic in Moscow 24.03.20 005 (14).jpg|250px|thumb|[[Moscow Metro]] on 25 March]]\n[[File:COVID-19 pandemic in Moscow 24.03.20 005 (56).jpg|250px|thumb|[[Yaroslavsky suburban direction of Moscow Railway]] on 25 March]]\n\nOn 23 January, the Russian city of [[Blagoveshchensk]], near the [[China\u2013Russia border|Chinese border]], limited access to the country. [[Cultural diplomacy|Cultural exchange]] and official visits to China were cancelled. The Governors of the [[Amur Oblast]] [[Vasily Orlov]], and of the [[Penza Oblast]] [[Ivan Belozertsev]], called on residents to abandon trips to China altogether. Residents of large cities were told to avoid contact with tourists from China.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sputniknews.com/world/202001231078113159-you-shall-not-pass-russian-border-city-to-limit-access-to-china-due-to-coronavirus-outbreak/|title=You Shall Not Pass! Russian Border City to Limit Access to China Due to coronavirus pandemic|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200123141329/https://sputniknews.com/world/202001231078113159-you-shall-not-pass-russian-border-city-to-limit-access-to-china-due-to-coronavirus-outbreak/|archive-date=23 January 2020|accessdate=25 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 January, Deputy Prime Minister [[Tatiana Golikova]] said Russia will restrict the entry of foreigners arriving from [[China]], except for flights to [[Moscow Sheremetyevo Airport]].<ref name=\"mwt\">[https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2020/03/07/coronavirus-in-russia-the-latest-news-march-8-a69117 Coronavirus in Russia: The Latest News]</ref>\n\nOn 20 February, the entry of [[Chinese nationality law|Chinese citizens]] was banned. The temporary suspension is for Chinese citizens entering Russia for employment, private, educational and tourist purposes.<ref name=\"mwt\" />\n\nOn 28 February, Moscow announced that it would deport 88 foreigners for allegedly violating quarantine measures.<ref name=\":4\" /> Russia barred [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Iran|Iranian]] citizens from entering Russia and said it would also restrict the entry of [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in South Korea|South Korean]] citizens from 1 March. Flights between Russia and South Korea are suspended, except for those operated by [[Aeroflot]] and [[Aurora (airline)|Aurora]].<ref name=\"mwt\" />\n\nOn 4 March, Russia suspended its train service from Moscow to [[Nice]], [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in France|France]].<ref name=\"mwt\" />\nAeroflot suspended flights to and from [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Hong Kong|Hong Kong]] since 9 March.<ref name=\"mwt\" />\n\nFlights to and from Italy, [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Germany|Germany]], [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in France|France]] and [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Spain|Spain]] are limited since 13 March. Russia also stopped issuing tourist visas to Italian citizens and closed the border to Italian citizens and foreigners coming from Italy.<ref name=\"mwt\" />\n\nOn 15 March, the land borders with [[Norway\u2013Russia border|Norway]] and [[Poland\u2013Russia border|Poland]] were closed to all foreigners. [[Russian Railways]] announced it would stop passenger trains from [[Moscow]] to [[Berlin]] and [[Paris]]. Earlier it was announced that train connections to and from [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Ukraine|Ukraine]], [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Moldova|Moldova]] and [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Latvia|Latvia]] would be suspended because those countries had closed their borders.<ref name=\"mwt\" />\n\nSince 16 March, flights to and from the [[European Union]], [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Norway|Norway]] and [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Switzerland|Switzerland]] were limited to regular flights between capital cities ([[Geneva]] in the case of Switzerland) and [[Moscow Sheremetyevo Airport]], and charter flights.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russia restricts air travel to the EU, allowing only charter flights and planes headed to capital cities |url=https://meduza.io/en/news/2020/03/13/russia-restricts-air-travel-to-the-eu-allowing-only-charter-flights-and-planes-headed-to-capital-cities |accessdate=13 March 2020 |work=[[Meduza]] |date=13 March 2020}}</ref> [[Prime Minister of Russia|Prime Minister]] [[Mikhail Mishustin]] announced that [[Belarus\u2013Russia border|the border]] with [[Belarus]] has been closed for the movement of people and an entry ban for foreigners will be imposed from 18 March to 1 May.<ref>{{cite news|title=Russia closes border with Belarus over coronavirus|url=https://tass.com/politics/1130493|accessdate=15 March 2020|work=[[TASS]]|date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Russia to impose entry ban for foreigners from March 18 to May 1 |url=https://tass.com/society/1130915 |accessdate=16 March 2020 |work=[[TASS]] |date=16 March 2020}}</ref> On 17 March, [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Russia)|Ministry of Foreign Affairs]] said Russian embassies and consulates had stopped issuing all types of visas, including e-visas, with exceptions for diplomats, people attending funerals and transit passengers.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0417\u0430\u044f\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043e\u0444\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044f \u041c\u0418\u0414 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u041c.\u0412.\u0417\u0430\u0445\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u0432 \u0441\u0432\u044f\u0437\u0438 \u0441 \u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u043c \u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435\u043c \u0432\u044a\u0435\u0437\u0434\u0430 \u0432 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0443\u044e \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0446\u0438\u044e \u0438\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0433\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0434\u0430\u043d \u0438 \u043b\u0438\u0446 \u0431\u0435\u0437 \u0433\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0434\u0430\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 |url=https://www.mid.ru/ru/foreign_policy/news/-/asset_publisher/cKNonkJE02Bw/content/id/4089464 |publisher=[[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Russia)|Ministry of Foreign Affairs]] |accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 March, Russia restricted [[air travel]] from all over the world, except for certain flights from Moscow to major capitals, and charter flights intended to move foreign citizens to their respective countries and [[Citizenship of Russia|Russian nationals]] back to Russia, until everyone is evacuated.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u044f \u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0438\u043b\u0430 \u0430\u0432\u0438\u0430\u0441\u043e\u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0441\u043e \u0432\u0441\u0435\u043c\u0438 \u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043c\u0438 \u0438\u0437-\u0437\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 |url=https://ria.ru/20200323/1568989250.html |accessdate=23 March 2020 |agency=RIA Novosti |date=23 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 March, the Russian government loosened the travel ban to allow the entry for relatives of Russian citizens.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u041a\u0430\u0431\u043c\u0438\u043d \u0440\u0430\u0437\u0440\u0435\u0448\u0438\u043b \u0432\u044a\u0435\u0437\u0434 \u0432 \u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0443 \u0438\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0446\u0430\u043c \u2014 \u0440\u043e\u0434\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430\u043c \u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u044f\u043d \u041f\u043e\u0434\u0440\u043e\u0431\u043d\u0435\u0435 \u043d\u0430 \u0420\u0411\u041a |url=https://www.rbc.ru/society/26/03/2020/5e7cae179a794707bc5f7934 |accessdate=26 March 2020 |work=[[RBK Group|RBK]] |date=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nAll regular and charter international flights were suspended on 27 March, except for those aimed at bringing Russians home.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russian government rules to suspend all flights to foreign countries |url=https://tass.com/economy/1135639 |accessdate=26 March 2020 |work=[[TASS]] |date=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn the same day, [[Grozny Airport]] refused to receive passengers without permanent or temporary registration in Chechnya.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0410\u044d\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442 \u0413\u0440\u043e\u0437\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043d\u0435 \u0431\u0443\u0434\u0435\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043c\u0430\u0442\u044c \u043f\u0430\u0441\u0441\u0430\u0436\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432 \u0438\u0437 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u044b \u0431\u0435\u0437 \u0440\u0435\u0433\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0432 \u0427\u0435\u0447\u043d\u0435 - \u0430\u0434\u043c\u0438\u043d\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u0446\u0438\u044f |url=http://www.interfax-russia.ru/Moscow/special.asp?sec=1752&id=1117051 |accessdate=27 March 2020 |agency=Interfax |date=27 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref>\n\nFollowing a request from the [[Government of Moscow]],<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u044b \u043f\u043e\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0438\u043b\u0438 BlaBlaCar \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0442\u044c \u0432\u0441\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u0435\u0437\u0434\u043a\u0438 |url=https://tass.ru/obschestvo/8079187 |accessdate=27 March 2020 |agency=TASS |date=25 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref> [[BlaBlaCar]] carpooling service decided to suspend its activities across Russia starting from 30 March.<ref>{{cite news |title=Blablacar \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0430\u0432\u043b\u0438\u0432\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0443 \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0432\u0438\u0441\u0430 \u0432 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 |url=https://tass.ru/ekonomika/8100837 |accessdate=27 March 2020 |agency=TASS |date=27 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 March, the Russian government decided to close all automobile, railway, pedestrian, river, or other [[border checkpoint]]s, including on the [[Belarus\u2013Russia border|Belarus border]], with exceptions similar to that of the air travel restrictions. The ban must be enforced on 30 March.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u041f\u0440\u0438\u043d\u044f\u0442\u043e \u0440\u0435\u0448\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043e \u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u043c \u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0438 \u0434\u0432\u0438\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0447\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0437 \u0430\u0432\u0442\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0431\u0438\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0435, \u0436\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0437\u043d\u043e\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0436\u043d\u044b\u0435, \u043f\u0435\u0448\u0435\u0445\u043e\u0434\u043d\u044b\u0435, \u0440\u0435\u0447\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u0438 \u0441\u043c\u0435\u0448\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043f\u0443\u043d\u043a\u0442\u044b \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0443\u0441\u043a\u0430 \u0447\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0437 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u0443\u044e \u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0443 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438, \u0430 \u0442\u0430\u043a\u0436\u0435 \u0447\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0437 \u0441\u0443\u0445\u043e\u043f\u0443\u0442\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0443\u0447\u0430\u0441\u0442\u043e\u043a \u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u043e-\u0431\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0446\u044b |url=http://government.ru/docs/39307/ |website=Government of Russia |accessdate=28 March 2020 |language=ru |date=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Nationwide measures ===\n[[File:Vladimir Putin visited the Coronavirus Monitoring Center (2020-03-17) 06.jpg|thumb|250px|President Putin, Prime Minister [[Mikhail Mishustin]] and Moscow Mayor [[Sergey Sobyanin]] visited the Coronavirus Monitoring Center on 17 March]]\n[[File:\u041f\u043e\u0441\u0435\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043a\u043e\u043b-\u0446\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0440\u0430 \u0414\u0435\u043f\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0430 \u0437\u0434\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u043e\u0445\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u044b (\u0421. \u0421\u043e\u0431\u044f\u043d\u0438\u043d) 3.jpg|thumb|250px|Call centre for the coronavirus situation in Moscow at [[Khodynsky Boulevard]] located in the gym of school No. 1409.<ref>[https://www.kp.ru/daily/27103/4177306/ \u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0435\u0439 \u0421\u043e\u0431\u044f\u043d\u0438\u043d \u043f\u043e\u0441\u0435\u0442\u0438\u043b call-\u0446\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0440 \u043f\u043e \u0441\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c \u0432 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0435: \u041c\u044b \u043f\u043e\u0431\u0435\u0434\u0438\u043c \u044d\u0442\u0443 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u043c\u0443]</ref>]]\n\nOn 14 and 15 March, [[Ministry of Education (Russia)|Ministry of Education]] and [[Ministry of Science and Higher Education (Russia)|Ministry of Science and Higher Education]] recommended regions to switch the educational process to [[distance learning]] if it is necessary.<ref name=\"mwt\" /><ref>{{cite news |title=Moscow schools start rolling out 'flexible attendance' and remote learning policies to fight coronavirus spread |url=https://meduza.io/en/feature/2020/03/14/moscow-schools-start-rolling-out-flexible-attendance-and-remote-learning-policies-to-fight-coronavirus-spread |accessdate=14 March 2020 |work=[[Meduza]] |date=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 March, [[Ministry of Culture (Russia)|Ministry of Culture]] announced closing all cultural institutions under its jurisdiction, including museums, theaters, symphonies, and circuses.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russia to close all federal theaters, museums, symphonies, and circuses |url=https://meduza.io/en/news/2020/03/17/russia-to-close-all-federal-theaters-museums-symphonies-and-circuses |accessdate=17 March 2020 |work=[[Meduza]] |date=17 March 2020}}</ref> On the same day, President Vladimir Putin said that the situation was \"generally under control\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.kremlin.ru/events/president/news/63001|title=Meeting with Government members|date=17 March 2020|website=Kremlin.ru}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 March, [[Ministry of Education (Russia)|Minister of Education]] [[Sergey Kravtsov (politician)|Sergey Kravtsov]] announced that all Russian schools would be closed from 23 March to 12 April.<ref name=\"mwt\" />\n\nOn 19 March, Russia's [[Rospotrebnadzor|Chief Sanitary Doctor]] Anna Popova required all people arriving from abroad to undergo a two-week self-isolation.<ref>{{cite news |title=All people arriving in Russia must undergo 14-day self-isolation |url=https://tass.com/society/1132439 |accessdate=19 March 2020 |agency=TASS |date=19 March 2020}}</ref> Russian courts stopped considering all but most urgent cases because of the pandemic until 10 April.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russian Courts Put Most Work on Pause Over Coronavirus |url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2020/03/19/russian-courts-put-most-work-on-pause-over-coronavirus-a69676 |accessdate=24 March 2020 |work=[[The Moscow Times]] |date=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, the Russian government adopted a number of decisions, including an instruction to regional authorities to suspend activities of any [[night club]]s, cinemas, children's entertainment centers, and to ban [[hookah]] smoking at any restaurants or cafes.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u041e \u0440\u0435\u0448\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f\u0445 \u043f\u043e \u0438\u0442\u043e\u0433\u0430\u043c \u0437\u0430\u0441\u0435\u0434\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043e\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0448\u0442\u0430\u0431\u0430 \u043f\u043e \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0443\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0436\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044e \u0437\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0437\u0430 \u0438 \u0440\u0430\u0441\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0442\u0435\u0440\u0440\u0438\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0438 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 |url=http://government.ru/orders/selection/401/39260/ |website=Government of Russia |accessdate=24 March 2020 |language=ru |date=24 March 2020}}</ref> The [[Central Bank of Russia|Central Bank]] recommended all the banks to keep the money for 3\u20134 days before giving it to clients or loading it into ATMs, and to restrict usage of cash recycling ATMs.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0420\u0435\u043a\u043e\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0434\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0431\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0430\u043c: \u043d\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0447\u043d\u043e\u0435 \u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 |url=https://cbr.ru/press/event/?id=6561 |website=Central Bank of Russia |accessdate=24 March 2020 |language=ru |date=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 March, President Putin, in a televised address to the nation, announced that the [[2020 Russian constitutional referendum]] would be postponed due to the coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://tass.ru/politika/8075213|title=\u041f\u0443\u0442\u0438\u043d: \u0434\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0433\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043f\u043e \u043f\u043e\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0430\u043c \u043a \u041a\u043e\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0434\u043e\u043b\u0436\u043d\u0430 \u0431\u044b\u0442\u044c \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0441\u0435\u043d\u0430|agency=[[TASS]]|date=25 March 2020}}</ref> He added that the next week would be a nationwide paid holiday and urged Russians to stay at home.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://tass.com/society/1135339|title=Putin calls on Russians 'to stay home' due to coronavirus|agency=[[TASS]]|date=25 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"mt-mar25\">{{cite web|url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2020/03/25/coronavirus-in-russia-the-latest-news-march-25-a69117|title=Coronavirus in Russia: The Latest News - March 25|website=[[The Moscow Times]]|date=25 March 2020}}</ref> Putin also announced a list of measures of [[social protection]], support for [[small and medium-sized enterprises]], and changes in [[fiscal policy]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Address to the Nation |url=http://en.kremlin.ru/events/president/news/63061 |website=President of Russia |accessdate=25 March 2020 |date=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 March, [[Ministry of Science and Higher Education (Russia)|Minister of Science and Higher Education]] [[Valery Falkov]] ordered all universities to close from March 28 to April 5.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russian students to go on recess on March 28 \u2014 April 5 |url=https://tass.com/society/1135613 |accessdate=26 March 2020 |work=[[TASS]] |date=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 March, as a follow-up to Putin's address to the nation, Prime Minister Mikhail Mishustin ordered all reservations at [[Pension (lodging)|pensions]] or [[Holiday cottage|holiday houses]] to be cancelled from 28 March to 1 June, recommended regional authorities to close all the [[piste]]s at resorts for the same period, instructed them to force all the public eating places (except for delivery services) to suspend activities from 28 March to 5 April, and recommend the citizens to refrain from travelling.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u041c\u0438\u0445\u0430\u0438\u043b \u041c\u0438\u0448\u0443\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d \u043f\u043e\u0440\u0443\u0447\u0438\u043b \u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0442\u044c \u0440\u0430\u0437\u043c\u0435\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0432 \u0441\u0430\u043d\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u044f\u0445, \u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0443 \u043a\u0443\u0440\u043e\u0440\u0442\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043e\u0431\u044a\u0435\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u0441\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043e\u0442\u0434\u044b\u0445\u0430 \u0438 \u0434\u0435\u044f\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044c \u043e\u0440\u0433\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0437\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043f\u0438\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f |url=http://government.ru/orders/selection/401/39288/ |website=Government of Russia |accessdate=27 March 2020 |language=ru |date=27 March 2020}}</ref> On the same day, the Ministry of Education announced the postponement of the [[Unified State Exam]] from the end of May to the beginning of June.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u041c\u0438\u043d\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0432\u0435\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0441\u043b\u043e \u0441\u0440\u043e\u043a\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0415\u0413\u042d |url=https://www.rbc.ru/society/27/03/2020/5e7dd7319a7947c713fa4a6a?utm_source=yxnews&utm_medium=desktop&utm_referrer=https%3A%2F%2Fyandex.ru%2Fnews |website=\u0420\u0411\u041a |accessdate=27 March 2020 |date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 March, as Moscow and Moscow Oblast declared a lockdown, Mishustin urged all regions to follow the example and take similar measures. He also announced a bill that would raise fines for breaching quarantine requirements.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u041c\u0438\u0448\u0443\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0437\u0432\u0430\u043b \u0440\u0435\u0433\u0438\u043e\u043d\u044b \u0431\u0440\u0430\u0442\u044c \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043c\u0435\u0440 \u0441 \u043c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0430 |url=https://www.interfax.ru/russia/701511 |accessdate=30 March 2020 |agency=Interfax |date=30 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=\u041c\u0438\u0448\u0443\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d \u043d\u0430\u0437\u0432\u0430\u043b \u043e\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0443\u044e \u0437\u0430\u0434\u0430\u0447\u0443 \u0432\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0435\u0439 \u0432\u043e \u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u044f \u0440\u0430\u0441\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 |url=https://tass.ru/obschestvo/8111725 |accessdate=30 March 2020 |agency=TASS |date=30 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 March, the [[Federal Assembly (Russia)|Federal Assembly]] approved a law allowing the [[Mikhail Mishustin's Cabinet|executive cabinet]] to declare a state of emergency on its own. Previously, only a commission led by the [[Minister of Emergency Situations (Russia)|Minister of Emergency Situations]] could do that.<ref>{{cite news |title=Legislation allowing prime minister's cabinet to declare state of emergency rockets through Russian legislative system |url=https://meduza.io/en/news/2020/03/31/legislation-allowing-prime-minister-s-cabinet-to-declare-state-of-emergency-rockets-through-russian-legislative-system |accessdate=31 March 2020 |work=[[Meduza.io]] |date=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 1 April, Prime Minister Mishustin and the [[Ministry of Digital Development, Communications and Mass Media (Russia)|Minister of Communications]] [[Maxut Shadayev]] announced creating a system of tracking quarantine violation based on data of [[List of mobile network operators of Europe#Russia|mobile network operators]]. Violators will receive a text message, and if they breach it systematically, the information will be sent to the police.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u041c\u0438\u043d\u043a\u043e\u043c\u0441\u0432\u044f\u0437\u0438 \u0440\u0430\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u043e \u0441\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0435\u043c\u0435 \u043e\u0442\u0441\u043b\u0435\u0436\u0438\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043d\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0448\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0430 |url=https://ria.ru/20200401/1569450769.html |accessdate=1 April 2020 |work=[[RIA Novosti]] |date=1 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 2 April, President Putin prolonged the non-working time until 30 April.<ref>{{cite news |title=Putin signs decree on non-working days for Russian citizens until April 30 |url=https://tass.com/politics/1139407 |accessdate=2 April 2020 |work=[[TASS]] |date=2 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Lockdowns ===\n[[File:COVID-19 pandemic lockdowns in Russia.svg|350px|thumb|Map of federal subjects that have announced the \"self-isolation regime\".\n{{legend|#003557|Full lockdown}}\n{{legend|#278dbf|Partial lockdown}}]]\n[[File:Coronavirus,_take_away_Putin.jpg|thumb|200px|Closed playground in Moscow]]\n\nOn 28 March, the Chechen authorities urged the population of the republic not to leave their places of permanent residence, and banned entry to [[Grozny]] for anyone except emergency services, food supplies, government officials, police, and journalists.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0427\u0420 \u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u0432\u044a\u0435\u0437\u0434 \u0432 \u0413\u0440\u043e\u0437\u043d\u044b\u0439 |url=https://chechnyatoday.com/news/334637 |accessdate=28 March 2020 |agency=\u0427\u0435\u0447\u043d\u044f \u0441\u0435\u0433\u043e\u0434\u043d\u044f |date=28 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref> On the next day, [[Chechnya]] closed its borders, with a full lockdown coming into effect on 30 March.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russia\u2019s Chechnya closes administratieve borders amid coronavirus outbreak |url=https://tass.com/russia/1137037 |accessdate=29 March 2020 |work=[[TASS]] |date=29 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 29 March, Moscow issued a [[stay-at-home order]] for all residents starting on 30 March. Muscovites will not be allowed to leave their homes except in cases of emergency medical care and other threats to life and health, to travel to work for those who are obliged to, to make purchases in the nearest store or pharmacy, to walk pets at a distance not exceeding 100 metres from the place of residence, as well as to take out the garbage. People have to keep a distance of 1.5 metres. Recently unemployed will get 19,500 rubles a month.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u041a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441. \u041e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0432\u0438\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043f\u043e \u0433\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0443 \u0438 \u0441\u043e\u0446\u0438\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0436\u043a\u0430 |url=https://www.sobyanin.ru/koronavirus-ogranichenie-peredvizheniya-i-sospodderzhka-grazhdan |accessdate=29 March 2020 |work=Sergey Sobyanin website |date=29 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0435 \u0432\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0443\u0442 \u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c \u0432\u0441\u0435\u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0439 \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0438\u0437\u043e\u043b\u044f\u0446\u0438\u0438 |url=https://ria.ru/20200329/1569323145.html |accessdate=29 March 2020 |work=\u0420\u0418\u0410 \u041d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438|date=29 March 2020}}</ref> After that, a similar regime was introduced in Moscow Oblast at 20:00 [[Moscow Time|MSK]] on 29 March.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0420\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0438\u0437\u043e\u043b\u044f\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0432\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0438\u0442\u0441\u044f \u0434\u043b\u044f \u0432\u0441\u0435\u0445 \u0436\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0439 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438 |url=https://mosreg.ru/sobytiya/novosti/news-submoscow/v-podmoskove-vvoditsya-rezhim-samoizolyatsii-dlya-vsekh-zhiteley |accessdate=29 March 2020 |work=Governor of Moscow Oblast official website|date=29 March 2020}}</ref> Senator [[Andrey Klishas]], chair of the Federation Council Committee on constitutional legislation and state construction, criticized this decision, saying that such restrictions are the exclusive competence of the [[Federal Assembly (Russia)|Federal Assembly]] and the [[President of Russia|President]].<ref>{{cite news |title=\u041a\u043b\u0438\u0448\u0430\u0441 \u043e\u0431 \u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f\u0445 \u0432 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0435: \u0442\u0430\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u043c\u0435\u0440\u044b \u2014 \u0438\u0441\u043a\u043b\u044e\u0447\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u043a\u043e\u043c\u043f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u043d\u0446\u0438\u044f \u043f\u0430\u0440\u043b\u0430\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0430 \u0438 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0437\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0430 |url=https://www.kommersant.ru/doc/4308072 |accessdate=29 March 2020 |work=\u041a\u043e\u043c\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0442\u044a|date=29 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 March, similar orders were announced in [[Adygea]], the [[Komi Republic]], [[Mari El]], [[Tatarstan]], [[Chuvashia]], some districts of [[Yakutia]], [[Arkhangelsk Oblast|Arkhangelsk]], [[Astrakhan Oblast|Astrakhan]],<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u0410\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u0445\u0430\u043d\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0432\u0432\u0435\u043b\u0438 \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043d \u0438\u0437-\u0437\u0430 \u0441\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c |url=https://kaspyinfo.ru/srochnoe-zajavlenie-astrahanskaja-oblast-perehodit-na-rezhim-vseobshhej-samoizoljacii/ |accessdate=30 March 2020 |work=KaspiyInfo |date=30 March 2020}}</ref> [[Belgorod Oblast|Belgorod]], [[Irkutsk Oblast|Irkutsk]], [[Kaliningrad Oblast|Kaliningrad]], [[Kursk Oblast|Kursk]], [[Lipetsk Oblast|Lipetsk]], [[Murmansk Oblast|Murmansk]], [[Nizhny Novgorod Oblast|Nizhny Novgorod]], [[Novgorod Oblast|Novgorod]], [[Ryazan Oblast|Ryazan]], [[Saratov Oblast|Saratov]], [[Sverdlovsk Oblast|Sverdlovsk]], [[Ulyanovsk Oblast|Ulyanovsk]] and [[Vologda Oblast|Vologda]] oblasts, the cities of [[Bryansk]] and Saint Petersburg.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u041f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0435 \u0432\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043d \u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0438\u0437\u043e\u043b\u044f\u0446\u0438\u0438. \u0422\u0435\u043f\u0435\u0440\u044c \u043a\u0430\u043a \u0432 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0435 |url=https://fontanka.ru/2020/03/30/69060805/ |accessdate=30 March 2020 |publisher=Fontanka |date=30 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref><ref name=\"lockdown\">{{cite news |title=Which regions of Russia are sheltering in place? A running list |url=https://meduza.io/en/feature/2020/03/30/which-regions-of-russia-are-sheltering-in-place |accessdate=30 March 2020 |work=[[Meduza]] |date=30 March 2020}}</ref> [[Leningrad Oblast]] banned movement of people between districts and introduced a lockdown in the town of {{ill|Murino|ru|\u041c\u0443\u0440\u0438\u043d\u043e}}.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u041b\u0435\u043d\u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0432\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0438\u0442\u0441\u044f \u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043d\u0430 \u0432\u044b\u0435\u0437\u0434 \u0437\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043b\u044b \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0436\u0438\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f |url=https://tass.ru/obschestvo/8115959 |accessdate=30 March 2020 |agency=TASS |date=30 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 March, the \"self-isolation regime\" was announced in republics of [[Altai Republic|Altai]], [[Bashkortostan]], [[Buryatia]], [[Dagestan]],<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u0414\u0430\u0433\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0435 \u0432\u0432\u0435\u043b\u0438 \u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0438\u0437\u043e\u043b\u044f\u0446\u0438\u0438 |url=https://ria.ru/20200331/1569421526.html |accessdate=31 March 2020 |work=[[RIA Novosti]] |date=31 March 2020}}</ref> [[Ingushetia]], [[Kabardino-Balkaria]], [[Kalmykia]], [[Karachay-Cherkessia]], [[Republic of Karelia|Karelia]],<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0435\u043b\u0438\u0438 \u0432\u0432\u0435\u043b\u0438 \u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0438\u0437\u043e\u043b\u044f\u0446\u0438\u0438 |url=https://ria.ru/20200331/1569413191.html |accessdate=31 March 2020 |work=[[RIA Novosti]] |date=31 March 2020}}</ref> [[Khakassia]], [[Mordovia]], [[Udmurtia]] and [[Tuva]], [[Altai Krai|Altai]], [[Khabarovsk Krai|Khabarovsk]] (for those over 65), [[Krasnodar Krai|Krasnodar]], [[Krasnoyarsk Krai|Krasnoyarsk]], [[Perm Krai|Perm]], [[Primorsky Krai|Primorsky]], [[Stavropol Krai|Stavropol]] and [[Zabaykalsky Krai|Zabaykalsky]] krais, [[Bryansk Oblast|Bryansk]], [[Chelyabinsk Oblast|Chelyabinsk]], [[Kaluga Oblast|Kaluga]], [[Kemerovo Oblast|Kemerovo]], [[Kirov Oblast|Kirov]], [[Kostroma Oblast|Kostroma]],<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u041a\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043c\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0432\u0432\u0435\u043b\u0438 \u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c \u043e\u0431\u044f\u0437\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0438\u0437\u043e\u043b\u044f\u0446\u0438\u0438 |url=https://ria.ru/20200331/1569412562.html |accessdate=31 March 2020 |work=[[RIA Novosti]] |date=31 March 2020}}</ref> [[Kurgan Oblast|Kurgan]], [[Magadan Oblast|Magadan]], [[Novosibirsk Oblast|Novosibirsk]], [[Omsk Oblast|Omsk]],<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412\u0441\u0435 \u0441\u0438\u0431\u0438\u0440\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u0440\u0435\u0433\u0438\u043e\u043d\u044b \u0432\u0432\u0435\u043b\u0438 \u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0438\u0437\u043e\u043b\u044f\u0446\u043